b'[<p><i><b>UFC 52: Couture vs. Liddell 2</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on April 16, 2005, at the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/MGM_Grand_Arena" title="MGM Grand Arena">MGM Grand Arena</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Las_Vegas,_Nevada" title="Las Vegas, Nevada">Las Vegas, Nevada</a>. The event was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Pay-per-view" title="Pay-per-view">pay-per-view</a> in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> and <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a>, and later released on <a href="/wiki/DVD" title="DVD">DVD</a>.\n</p>, <p>Headlining the card were the coaches of <a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter" title="The Ultimate Fighter">The Ultimate Fighter</a>, <a href="/wiki/Randy_Couture" title="Randy Couture">Randy Couture</a> and <a href="/wiki/Chuck_Liddell" title="Chuck Liddell">Chuck Liddell</a>. At the time, it was the highest-grossing UFC event ever at the live gate, with $2,575,450 in ticket sales.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Dan_Severn" title="Dan Severn">Dan "The Beast" Severn</a> was inducted into the UFC Hall of Fame at this event.\n</p>, <p>The total fighter payroll for UFC 52 was $519,500.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The rematch bout between <a href="/wiki/Matt_Hughes_(fighter)" title="Matt Hughes (fighter)">Matt Hughes</a> and <a href="/wiki/Frank_Trigg" title="Frank Trigg">Frank Trigg</a> for the Welterweight title is one of president of the UFC <a href="/wiki/Dana_White" title="Dana White">Dana White</a>\'s favorite fights.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-hallfame_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-hallfame-4">[4]</a></sup> In 2015 during International Fight Week, this became the second fight to be inducted into the <a href="/wiki/UFC_Hall_of_Fame" title="UFC Hall of Fame">UFC Hall of Fame</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-hallfame_4-1"><a href="#cite_note-hallfame-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>]'